transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, Joanna speaking, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Is this Joanna?

Speaker 1: Yes, it is, sir.

Speaker 2: My name is Troy Miller, and I live down here in Daytona Beach, Florida, and I'd call and you give me your number and extension in case I have a problem, you know?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: With my order, you know?

Speaker 1: Yeah, hi, Mr. Miller.

Speaker 2: Hey, would you check my mailing address for me?

Speaker 1: Because the package, it went from Cincinnati, Ohio, to Kentucky, to Greensboro, North Carolina, to Jacksonville, Florida, now it went back to Greensboro, North Carolina,

Speaker 2: and I called the UPS store and they tracked it, but they said it's in the Postal Service's hands now,

Speaker 1: so I went out to the Postal Service and I talked to the Postmaster and she checked on it

Speaker 2: and she says she thinks it went back to Greensboro, Ohio, and anyway, she scanned it.

Speaker 1: Anyway, she's supposed to get back to me, but I just wanted to make sure you wrote my address down right, you know?

Speaker 2: Yeah, of course, and I'm checking on the tracking as well to see what happened there.

Speaker 1: You're not the first person to call in if that's happened.

Speaker 2: I don't know, because there is an alert saying that winter weather in the southwest, Great Plains, Midwest,

Speaker 1: Great Lakes, Ohio Valley, southeast, and northeast regions of the U.S. may delay final delivery due to some weather.

Speaker 2: I understand why, but I couldn't understand why it went to Jacksonville and then it went back to—

Speaker 1: it came from Greensboro, North Carolina, to Jacksonville, and it went back to North Carolina again.

Speaker 2: I don't understand that because, you know, that's where I was.

Speaker 1: I had one like that yesterday, too, where it was like, why would they?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that doesn't make sense that it would go all the way across the country.

Speaker 1: So let me just confirm the address I have is 165 Hernandez Ave, Ormond Beach, Florida, 32174.

Speaker 2: That's right.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's what was the shipping address.

Speaker 1: So I would say give it a couple more days, and if you don't receive it by this Friday, I can send you a replacement order at no cost.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I'll let you know.

Speaker 2: I'll let you know for sure.

Speaker 1: That's good.

Speaker 2: It makes me feel better.

Speaker 1: At least everything was on point, you know.

Speaker 2: Yeah, there wasn't any errors on our end.

Speaker 1: I am so sorry for the delay because it was shipped out on the 22nd, so it should have arrived to you by now.

Speaker 2: But I think, again, there's the U.S. Postal Service.

Speaker 1: You're not the first person to call in.

Speaker 2: I think that this severe weather is perhaps causing them to reroute packages.

Speaker 1: But let's give it one more day to kind of see where it goes next, and then if not, I'm happy to send you a replacement.

Speaker 2: So what do you want me to do?

Speaker 1: Just like if it don't come tomorrow, what's today, Tuesday or Wednesday?

Speaker 2: Yeah, Tuesday.

Speaker 1: Is today Tuesday?

Speaker 2: Today is Tuesday, yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So if I don't see it, I don't know what.

Speaker 1: Call me on Thursday.

Speaker 2: That way we can ensure it gets sent out this week.

Speaker 1: Let's not wait until Friday.

Speaker 2: So call me on Thursday if you don't get it by then.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Where are you at in this?

Speaker 1: Are you in California?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: So it's 4-22 here.

Speaker 2: What time is it out there?

Speaker 1: 1-22.

Speaker 2: Oh, that's 1-22, 3-22.

Speaker 1: So what, are you three hours behind?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Well, I sure appreciate it.

Speaker 2: I'm here from 8 a.m. to 3 p.m. Pacific Standard.

Speaker 1: Every day?

Speaker 2: Monday through Friday, yes.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, I appreciate your help.

Speaker 1: Yeah, my pleasure.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'll send you a replacement if you don't get it by this Thursday.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: My pleasure.

Speaker 2: Thanks for calling in, sir.

Speaker 1: Sorry about that.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: You, too.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
